em"], "i": [471, 8293, 1189, 8278, 5755]}}, {"q": "If you can imagine it, you can achieve it. If you can dream it, you can become it.", "d": {"d": ["William Arthur Ward", "You", "Dream", "Achieve", "Become", "Imagine"], "i": [16829, 8278, 2148, 66, 623, 3721]}}, {"q": "Respect your parents. What they tell you is true. Hard work, dedication and faith will get you anything. Imagination will drive itself. You can get anything you want, but you have to have faith behind all your ideas. Stick to your goals and have an undying faith.", "d": {"d": ["Russell Simmons", "Hard Work", "Work", "Faith", "You"], "i": [14358, 3375, 8204, 2596, 8278]}}, {"q": "Dolls fire our collective imagination, for better and - too often - for worse. From life-size dolls the same height as the little girls who carry them, to dolls whose long hair can 'grow' longer, to Barbie and her fashionable sisters, dolls do double duty as child's play and the focus of adult art and adult fear.", "d": {"d": ["Ellen Datlow", "Fire", "Fear", "Art", "Focus"], "i": [4793, 2741, 2655, 373, 2800]}}, {"q": "To invent, you need a good imagination and a pile of junk.", "d": {"d": ["Thomas A. Edison", "Good", "You", "Need", "Invent", "Junk"], "i": [15853, 3117, 8278, 4936, 3968, 4078]}}, {"q": "If you want a vision of the future, imagine a boot stamping on a human face - forever.", "d": {"d": ["George Orwell", "Future", "Face", "You", "Vision"], "i": [5816, 2963, 2567, 8278, 7960]}}, {"q": "Those who have learned to walk on the threshold of the unknown worlds, by means of what are commonly termed par excellence the exact sciences, may then, with the fair white wings of imagination, hope to soar further into the unexplored amidst which we live.", "d": {"d": ["Ada Lovelace", "Hope", "Walk", "White", "Excellence"], "i": [108, 3561, 7999, 8113, 2481]}}, {"q": "We are so obsessed with doing that we have no time and no imagination left for being. As a result, men are valued not for what they are but for what they do or what